# Project Preferences

## Python Environment
- Always use `uv` for Python package management
- Always use a virtual environment (venv) for Python projects
- Activate venv with: `source .venv/bin/activate`
- Create venv with: `uv venv`
- Install packages with: `uv pip install <package>`

## Code Style
- Follow Python best practices and PEP 8
- Use type hints where appropriate
- Include error handling and logging

## GitHub Organization
- Always push repositories to the organization: https://github.com/orgs/svc-bi-concepts
- Do not create repositories under personal account
- Use GitHub CLI (`gh`) for repository management when possible
